        <title>Piping</title>
        <paragraph>The AguaClara plant uses PVC pipe and fittings for all plumbing with the exception of:</paragraph>
        <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>The inlet, outlet, and drainage pipe that is exposed outside the building (<number_reference internal="True" refid="figure-moroceli" title="Fig. %s"><inline classes="std std-numref">Fig. 3</inline></number_reference>). Galvanized iron pipes and fittings are used here because of their durability.</paragraph>
            </list_item>
            <list_item>
                <paragraph>Some connections of the chemical dosing systems, which have to be flexible (<reference internal="True" refuri="../Chemical_Dosing/Dosing_Purpose_and_Description#title-dosing-proposito-y-descripcion"><inline classes="std std-ref">Purpose and Description</inline></reference>). Various hose sizes are used.</paragraph>
            </list_item>
        </enumerated_list>
        <paragraph>There are no high static pressures in the plant, as the highest pressure is at the bottom of the filter, which is <problematic ids="id3" refid="id2">|H.Fi|</problematic> deep, and does not exceed 7 psi. The thinner drainage pipe could withstand the pressure at any point in the plant, and therefore pipe specifications are not based on pressures but on overall durability and other practical considerations.</paragraph>
        <target refid="figure-moroceli"></target>
        <figure align="center" ids="id1 figure-moroceli" names="figure_moroceli">
            <image candidates="{'*': 'Construction_Materials\\Images/moroceli.png'}" uri="Construction_Materials\Images/moroceli.png" width="400px"></image>
            <caption>The galvanized iron inlet pipe of the AguaClara plant in Morocelí, El Paraíso.</caption>
        </figure>
        <paragraph>It has been observed that small diameter, thin-walled pipes are deformed under the weight of the materials above them when melted into the brick walls built in the plant, causing water leaks. In addition, those exposed during normal operation are more likely to break. With larger diameter pipes the drainage specifications are thick enough not to deform when melted and withstand normal abuse in operation. As a general rule, plant pipe specifications are recommended based on the following guide:</paragraph>
